verses.text_plain: O sing unto the Lord a new song: sing unto the Lord, all the earth.
verses.verse_html: 1O sing unto the Lord a new song: sing unto the Lord, all the earth.

verses.text_plain: Sing unto the Lord, bless his name; shew forth his salvation from day to day.
verses.verse_html: 2Sing unto the Lord, bless his name; shew forth his salvation from day to day.

verses.text_plain: Declare his glory among the heathen, his wonders among all people.
verses.verse_html: 3Declare his glory among the heathen, his wonders among all people.

verses.text_plain: For the Lord is great, and greatly to be praised: he is to be feared above all gods.
verses.verse_html: 4For the Lord is great, and greatly to be praised: he is to be feared above all gods.

verses.text_plain: For all the gods of the nations are idols: but the Lord made the heavens.
verses.verse_html: 5For all the gods of the nations are idols: but the Lord made the heavens.

verses.text_plain: Honour and majesty are before him: strength and beauty are in his sanctuary.
verses.verse_html: 6Honour and majesty are before him: strength and beauty are in his sanctuary.

verses.text_plain: Give unto the Lord, O ye kindreds of the people, give unto the Lord glory and strength.
verses.verse_html: 7Give unto the Lord, O ye kindreds of the people, give unto the Lord glory and strength.

verses.text_plain: Give unto the Lord the glory due unto his name: bring an offering, and come into his courts.
verses.verse_html:
8Give unto the Lord the glory due unto his name: bring an offering, and come into his courts. ▼
▼ due…: Heb. of his name

footnotes.body_html: ▼ due…: Heb. of his name

verses.text_plain: O worship the Lord in the beauty of holiness: fear before him, all the earth.
verses.verse_html:
9O worship the Lord in the beauty of holiness: fear before him, all the earth. ▼
▼ in the…: or, in the glorious sanctuary

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in the…: or, in the glorious sanctuary
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in the…: or, in the glorious sanctuary

verses.text_plain: Say among the heathen that the Lord reigneth: the world also shall be established that it shall not be moved: he shall judge the people righteously.
verses.verse_html: 10Say among the heathen that the Lord reigneth: the world also shall be established that it shall not be moved: he shall judge the people righteously.

tokens.text: that it shall not be moved

verses.text_plain: Let the heavens rejoice, and let the earth be glad; let the sea roar, and the fulness thereof.
verses.verse_html:
11Let the heavens rejoice, and let the earth be glad; let the sea roar, and the fulness thereof. ▼
▼ the fulness…: or, all it containeth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the fulness…: or, all it containeth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the fulness…: or, all it containeth

verses.text_plain: Let the field be joyful, and all that is therein: then shall all the trees of the wood rejoice
verses.verse_html: 12Let the field be joyful, and all that is therein: then shall all the trees of the wood rejoice

tokens.text: therein: then shall all the trees

verses.text_plain: Before the Lord: for he cometh, for he cometh to judge the earth: he shall judge the world with righteousness, and the people with his truth.
verses.verse_html: 13Before the Lord: for he cometh, for he cometh to judge the earth: he shall judge the world with righteousness, and the people with his truth.
